.START 

Stephen W. Nagy, 49 years old, was named senior vice president of finance and chief financial officer of General Signal Corp. 

General Signal, which has interests in process control, electrical, semiconductor, transportation and telecommunications systems, hasn't had anyone in the post since January, when Theodore Wiedemann resigned for personal reasons. 

The company, which doesn't have a president, has three other senior vice presidents, who head its divisions.
All report to Edmund M. Carpenter, 48, chairman and chief executive officer.
The five top officers range in age from 48 to 52. 

Mr. Nagy had been vice president of finance and chief financial officer of Trinova Corp., a Maumee, Ohio, maker of machinery parts and plastics.
He joined Trinova in 1982 as corporate controller. 

